    public class Biclique<V extends java.lang.Comparable<? super V>,E extends java.lang.Comparable<? super E>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Biclique<V,E>>
    Class implements a complete bipartite graph (biclique) with methods for computing maximal bicliques.

    1.0, June 26th 2019.
    Author:

    • Method Detail

      • compare

        private int compare(java.util.Set<Graph.Vertex<V>> vset0,
                    java.util.Set<Graph.Vertex<V>> vset1)
        Compares two sets X, Y of vertices.

        It holds: X < Y <=>

        • size(X) < size(Y),
        • if size is equal, compare elementwise in ascending order, first difference is returned.
        Parameters:
        vset0 - First set of vertices.
        vset1 - Second set of vertices.
        Returns:
        Standard result of comparisons:
        • X < Y <=> compare(X, Y) < 0
        • X = Y <=> compare(X, Y) = 0
        • X > Y <=> compare(X, Y) > 0

      • consensus

        public java.util.Set<Biclique<V,E>> consensus(Biclique<V,E> other)
        Computes the consensus of two bicliques.

        From two bicliques (X1, Y1) and (X2, Y2) the consensus consists of the following bicliques (non empty intersection provided):

        • (X1 intersection X2, Y1 union Y2),
        • (X1 intersection Y2, Y1 union X2),
        • (Y1 intersection X2, X1 union Y2),
        • (Y1 intersection Y2, X1 union X2).
        Parameters:
        other - The other biclique.
        Returns:
        Consensus set of (0 to 4) maximal bicliques.

      • isAbsorbedOf

        public boolean isAbsorbedOf(java.util.Set<Biclique<V,E>> setOfBicliques)
        Tests if biclique is absorbed by any biclique of a set of bicliques.
        A biclique is absorbed by another byclique if both partitions of vertices are subsets of the partitions (swapped if applicable) of vertices of the other one.
        Parameters:
        setOfBicliques - Set of bicliques to test absorption.
        Returns:
        True if biclique is absorbed, false otherwise.
